  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    org.omnifaces.util.Faces.getForwardRequestQueryString()
    Since 2.4. This is abstracted away by Faces.getRequestQueryString(). Use it instead. JSF has as to retrieving request URI no business of knowing if the request is forwarded/rewritten or not.
    org.omnifaces.util.FacesLocal.getForwardRequestQueryString(FacesContext)
    Since 2.4. This is abstracted away by FacesLocal.getRequestQueryString(FacesContext). Use it instead. JSF has as to retrieving request URI no business of knowing if the request is forwarded/rewritten or not.
    org.omnifaces.util.Servlets.getForwardRequestQueryString(HttpServletRequest)
    Since 2.4. Use Servlets.getRequestQueryString(HttpServletRequest) instead.
    org.omnifaces.util.Faces.getForwardRequestURI()
    Since 2.4. This is abstracted away by Faces.getRequestURI(). Use it instead. JSF has as to retrieving request URI no business of knowing if the request is forwarded/rewritten or not.
    org.omnifaces.util.FacesLocal.getForwardRequestURI(FacesContext)
    Since 2.4. This is abstracted away by FacesLocal.getRequestURI(FacesContext). Use it instead. JSF has as to retrieving request URI no business of knowing if the request is forwarded/rewritten or not.
    org.omnifaces.util.Servlets.getForwardRequestURI(HttpServletRequest)
    Since 2.4. Use Servlets.getRequestURI(HttpServletRequest) instead.
    org.omnifaces.util.Faces.getForwardRequestURIWithQueryString()
    Since 2.4. This is abstracted away by Faces.getRequestURIWithQueryString(). Use it instead. JSF has as to retrieving request URI no business of knowing if the request is forwarded/rewritten or not.
    org.omnifaces.util.FacesLocal.getForwardRequestURIWithQueryString(FacesContext)
    Since 2.4. This is abstracted away by FacesLocal.getRequestURIWithQueryString(FacesContext). Use it instead. JSF has as to retrieving request URI no business of knowing if the request is forwarded/rewritten or not.
    org.omnifaces.util.Servlets.getForwardRequestURIWithQueryString(HttpServletRequest)
    Since 2.4. Use Servlets.getRequestURIWithQueryString(HttpServletRequest) instead.
    org.omnifaces.el.MethodReference.getMethodInfo()
    Since 2.5 this class already extends from MethodInfo.
